      "order": 1,
      "Description": "AI chatbots are becoming increasingly common in the hospitality industry, helping hotels, restaurants, and travel services handle customer enquiries around the clock. However, when a chatbot provides incorrect information about bookings, availability, pricing, or local recommendations, the consequences can range from minor inconveniences to serious complaints and lost revenue. This lesson explores the tension between delivering a smooth, engaging customer experience and ensuring the accuracy of the information chatbots provide. You will look at real-world examples of where things can go wrong, and consider practical steps that hospitality businesses can take to reduce the risks of errors. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to balance efficiency with reliability when using AI chatbots in a hospitality setting.",
